article.headline: Princeton 74, Harvard 68, 2 OT
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Lincoln Gunn had a career-high 22 points, five assists and four rebounds to lead Princeton to a 74-68 win over Harvard in double overtime on Friday night. Noah Savage added 16 points for the Tigers (10-9, 1-4 in Ivy League) and went 4-for-4 from the foul line in the final 20 seconds of the second overtime to seal the win. Luke Owings added 10 points and seven rebounds for Princeton. Drew Housman had a career-high 33 points, four assists and four rebounds for the Crimson (10-11, 3-4), while Andrew Pusar had 12 points and Evan Harris added 10. The teams traded baskets for most of regulation, which featured 13 lead changes and nine ties, but it ended tied at 56-56 when neither team could score in the final 1:46. In the first overtime, Housman scored all four of Harvard's points but he also missed two foul shots, while Princeton missed its chance when Michael Strittmatter's last-chance shot failed. Kyle Koncz then gave Princeton the lead for good when he hit a 3-pointer with 2:48 left in the second overtime, giving the Tigers a 65-62 lead. Housman then made two free throws, but Harvard could not get any closer.
